Specified by:
setRenderer in interface Feature

setTolerance

public static void setTolerance(float tolerance)
Sets the tolerance values used for contains() testing. Any location within a distance of the given tolerance of this point is considered to be at the same location. Note that this method is static, meaning that a single tolerance value is shared by all point objects.

Parameters:
tolerance - Tolerance distance in the same units as the point's coordinates.

contains

public boolean contains(float x,
                        float y)
Tests whether the given location matches this point. Coordinates should be in the same geographic units as the point feature.

Specified by:
contains in interface Feature
Parameters:
x - x coordinate in geographic coordinates.
y - y coordinate in geographic coordinates.
Returns:
True if the given point matches this point, false if not.
